OL,3,GYorkshire & Humber
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FA dry, fine
OL,6,Fevening, though rather breezy. A
OL,7,Flargely clear night will follow, and
OL,8,Fbecoming chilly with a risk of a rural
OL,9,Fgrass frost in sheltered spots. Winds
OL,10,Feasing inland but remaining brisk
OL,11,Facross the hills.
OL,12,
OL,13,CThursday:FAnother day of long sunny
OL,14,Fspells, though rather windy once
OL,15,Fagain, with the strongest winds near
OL,16,Fcoasts and across hills. Warm inland
OL,17,Fbut cooler along the coast.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
